Summary

There are currently 10 screens in the signup flow (pre-KYC). We use front-end tracking to determine when a user loads a screen and/or moves from one step to the other. Analysis was done with over a 14-day period as a simple overview. Numbers therefore shouldnt be read as gospel, but are directionally accurate. Funding conversion rates are as low as they are due to insufficient lead time but should also be directionally accurate as a comparison between different onboarding platforms.

TL;DR

  • Majority of the dropoff in the signup flow happens in the first couple screens
  • Android dominates the signup and KYC process, but iOS users close the funding and activity gap later (later activity data not presented here)
  • We see serious drops from Signup Complete (ie email_comfirmation screen) to KYC Complete and again to FT MAU
  • Additional followup investigation into screen design and UX needs to be done on the dropoff points
